# Validation ladder

Use the smallest command that proves the change.

1. One file → `pnpm --filter @sfcr/web exec vitest run test/<file>.test.ts(x) [--reporter=dot]`
2. Most `packages/web` → `pnpm web:test:fast`
3. Notebook source/navigation/editors/assistant → `pnpm web:test:integration`
4. Templates / model smoke → `pnpm web:test:templates`
5. Cross-package or pre-handoff → `pnpm typecheck` then `pnpm test`

Package tests: `@sfcr/core` and `@sfcr/chat-api` (Vitest); `@sfcr/core-worker` and `@sfcr/notebook-core` (compile-only — also `check:boundaries` for notebook-core). Worker protocol: `packages/web/test/workerHandler.test.ts`.

After schema/core changes: `pnpm typecheck`. After pilot notebook YAML: `pnpm --filter @sfcr/web compile:notebook-yaml -- --write`.

`pnpm --filter @sfcr/web test` is not the same as `web:test:fast` — prefer root shortcuts for iteration.
